                         FAQ
                    </span>
                    <h2 class="cs-title">Sprinkler & Irrigation Questions</h2>
                </div>
                <ul class="cs-faq-list">
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">How much is sprinkler system installation in Las Cruces?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Sprinkler system installation cost depends on yard size, number of zones, and system type. A basic drip zone starts around $1,500. A full underground sprinkler system installation for an average Las Cruces yard typically ranges from $2,500 to $5,000. We provide a detailed, line-item quote before any work begins.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">How do I find leaks in my sprinkler system?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Look for soggy spots, unusually green patches, or a water meter that keeps running when all zones are off. These are common signs of an underground leak. Our sprinkler repair service uses pressure testing and visual zone-by-zone checks to locate leaks quickly and fix them before they drive up your water bill.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">Should I use drip or sprinklers?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Drip irrigation works best for beds, trees, and xeriscape areas because it delivers water right to root zones with minimal evaporation. Sprinkler heads are better for turf and ground cover that need broad, even coverage. Most Las Cruces properties do best with a combination of both systems on separate zones.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">How long does a sprinkler system installation take?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Most residential lawn sprinkler system installations are completed in 1 to 3 days, depending on yard size and number of zones. We restore all trenching the same day so your yard looks clean when we leave. Larger commercial projects may take a week or more.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">What is a smart irrigation controller, and is it worth it?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>A smart irrigation controller connects to WiFi and adjusts watering based on real-time weather data, soil moisture, and seasonal changes. It skips watering on rainy or windy days automatically. Most Las Cruces homeowners save 20% to 40% on outdoor water use, so the controller often pays for itself within one to two seasons.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <details class="cs-faq">
                            <summary class="cs-faq-summary">
                                <span class="cs-faq-question">Do you offer sprinkler system blowout service for winter?</span>
                                <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24">
                                        <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"/>
                                    </svg>
                                </span>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="cs-faq-body">
                                <p>Las Cruces winters are mild, but we do get occasional hard freezes that can crack pipes and valves. We offer seasonal controller adjustments, valve checks, and sprinkler system blowout service to prevent freeze damage. We also reprogram your controller for a winter schedule so you are not over-watering during cooler months.</p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
